SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT
THIS SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT (this "Agreement"), is entered into as of June 20, 2018 (the "Effective Date"), by and between New Mexico Wind, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("NMW"), and Casa Mesa Wind, LLC, a Delaware limited liability company ("CMW"). NMW and CMW may be referred to herein individually as a "Party" and collectively as the "Parties."
RECITALS
WHEREAS, NMW leases and operates a wind turbine electrical generation facility, which, upon completion of turbine repowering, will have an aggregate nameplate capacity of approximately 204 MW, and related infrastructure on a site located in De Baca and Quay Counties, New Mexico, known as the New Mexico Wind Project (the "NMW Facility");
WHEREAS, CMW is developing and will lease and operate a wind turbine electrical generation facility, which, upon completion, will have a nameplate capacity of approximately 50.93 MW (which includes a 1 MW/l MWh battery system), and related infrastructure on a site located in De Baca and Quay Counties, New Mexico, known as the Casa Mesa Wind Project (the "CMW Facility");
WHEREAS, NMW (as successor and assignee of FPL Energy New Mexico Wind, LLC) is party to that certain Interconnection Agreement, dated May 27, 2003, with Public Service Company of New Mexico, assigned to NMW pursuant to that certain Assignment and Assumption Agreement, dated May 16, 2018 (as assigned and amended from time . to time, the "GIA"), and leases and operates certain interconnection facilities described in Appendix A of the GIA (the "Interconnection Facilities") and (collectively, with the NMW Facility and CMW Facility, the "Projects" and individually, a "Project");
WHEREAS, NMW leases and/or operates certain personal property, real property, fixtures, easements, equipment and/or facilities described in Exhibit A attached hereto (the "Shared Facilities") that are necessary for the operation and maintenance of the NMW Facility;
WHEREAS, NMW desires to grant CMW the right to utilize the Shared Facilities, on the terms and conditions set forth herein;
NOW THEREFORE, in consideration of the premises and of the mutual covenants and agreements contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and sufficiency of which is hereby acknowledged, the Parties hereby agree as follows:
AGREEMENT
1. TERM; EARLY TERMINATION
1.1 The term of this Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and shall continue in effect until terminated (a) by mutual agreement of the Parties or (b) pursuant to Section 1.2.
5
1.2 This Agreement shall automatically terminate, without further action by either Party and without further liability of one Party to the other, upon the date that each of NMW and CMW (or their successors and assigns) have permanently ceased operation of the Projects.
2. GRANT OF SHARED FACILITIES RJGHTS
2.1 NMW hereby grants to CMW, during the term of this Agreement and on the terms and subject to the conditions hereof, the non-exclusive right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities as may be reasonably necessary in connection with CMW's ownership or lease, operation and maintenance of the CMW Facility; ·' 2.2 NMW hereby acknowledges that CMW' s rights to access and utilize the Shared Facilities described in Exhibit A attached hereto are essential to the production of electric energy by the CMW Facility.
2.3 The right to access and utilize the Shared Facilities granted to CMW hereunder shall vest in CMW as a contracting party hereunder without any transfer of title or leasehold interest in the Shared Facilities. 3. NATURE OF SHARED FACILITIES RIGHTS 3.1 NMW grants the rights to CMW under this Agreement, to the extent that such rights do not (i) limit in any material respect the ability of NMW to perform its obligations under any agreement, as the same may be hereafter modified or amended, that NMW has entered into, or enters into after the date hereof or (ii) adversely affect the operations or profitability of NMW in any material respect.
3.2 Except as set forth in Section 6.8, CMW shall not assign or transfer the rights granted hereunder, or grant any permission, license, right of way or similar right to the rights granted hereunder, without the prior written consent of NMW.
3.3 Subject to the terms of this Agreement, NMW shall not take any action that results in the forbearance, foreclosure, termination or alteration of CMW's access to, utilization of or reliance upon the Shared Facilities without the prior written consent of CMW.
4. MAINTENANCE OF SHARED FACILITIES
4.1 NMW shall be responsible for the ownership or possession, operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Shared Facilities. The costs and expenses of the operation, inspection, maintenance, repair, alteration, relocation, improvement and replacement of the Shared Facilities shall be allocated pro rata between NMW and CMW based upon the relative megawatt percentage of the NMW Facility and the CMW Facility, respectively, to the total megawatts of the NMW Facility and the CMW Facility combined.
4.2 In the event that the NMW Facility and the CMW Facility are no longer operated and maintained by a single entity for any reason, the Parties agree to use good faith - ·efforts to negotiate mutually agreeable terms and execute a mutually agreeable agreement (or amendment to this Agreement) that specifies the division of responsibilities of the entities providing operation and maintenance services associated with the Shared Facilities for the NMW Facility and the CMW Facility.
5. CHANGE IN OWNERSHIP; CHANGE IN LAW
5.1 In the event that the membership interests of NMW and CMW are not at least 50% beneficially owned by the same direct or indirect entity, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate and implement (a) a mutually acceptable ownership structure of the Shared Facilities that provides for the common ownership of_the Shared Facilities by NMW and CMW and (b) mutually agreeable terms and execute a mutually agreeable agreement (or amendment to this Agreement)· that recognizes such common ownership of the Shared Facilities.
5 .2 In the event that a change in the laws or regulations applicable to the NMW Facility or the CMW Facility, or this Agreement requires the amendment, modification or replacement of this Agreement in order to satisfy any applicable federal or local regulatory requirements, the Parties agree to use good faith efforts to negotiate and implement mutually agreeable terms to accomplish such amendment, modification or replacement.
6. MISCELLANEOUS
6.1 Agreement to Cooperate. Each Party agrees to reasonably cooperate with the other Party so that, subject to the terms of this Agreement, each of the NMW Facility and the CMW Facility benefits from the full utilization and enjoyment of the Shared Facilities as is necessary for the efficient operation of each Project.
6.2 Relationship of Parties. (a) The Parties do not intend to create hereby any joint venture, partnership, association or any other entity for the conduct of any business, and (b) nothing herein shall be deemed to authorize either Party to act on behalf of the other Party.
6.3 Non-Interference. Each Party agrees not to interfere with the reasonable and necessary utilization of the Shared Facilities by the other Party as permitted hereunder.
6.4 Modification and Amendment. The terms of this Agreement may only be modified or amended in a writing signed by each Party.
6.5 Waiver. The failure of a Party to insist upon or enforce strict performance of any of the provisions of this Agreement or to exercise any rights or remedies under this Agreement shall not be construed as a waiver or relinquishment to any extent of such Party's right to assert or rely upon any such provisions, rights, and remedies in that or any other instance; rather, the same shall be and remain in full force and effect.
6.6 Enforceability. Any provision of this Agreement which is prohibited or unenforceable in any jurisdiction shall, as to such jurisdiction, be ineffective only to the
extent of such prohibition, but shall be effective to the extent of such remaining provisions hereof.
6.7 Transfer of Shared Facilities. Except as set forth in Section 6.8, NMW may not transfer, sell, assign or sub-lease its ownership, leasehold interest in the Shared Facilities or any portion thereof without the prior written consent of CMW.
6.8 Assignment. Neither Party may assign its rights or obligations hereunder without the prior written consent of the other Party, provided that either Party may collaterally assign this Agreement to any entity, or such entity's agent, in connection with a financing or a refinancing that is directly or indirectly secured in whole or in part by the NMW Facility or the CMW Facility, as applicable, and any actual· assignment or transfer to another party arising from the realization upon any such collateral assignment (including, without limitation, any purchaser at a foreclosure sale) shall also be permitted without the prior written consent of the other Party. This Agreement shall be binding upon and inure to the benefit of successors and permitted assigns of the Parties hereto.
6.9 [Intentionally Omitted].
6.10 Governing Law. This Agreement shall be governed by and constructed in accordance with the laws of the State of Florida without regard to its conflict of laws provisions.
6.11 Inspection of Records. Each Party shall have access to any records concerning the Shared Facilities held by the other Party upon reasonable notice and at reasonable times.
6.12 Section Headings. The section headings in this Agreement are for convenience of reference only and shall not modify, define, expand, or limit any of the terms or provisions hereof.
6.13 Counterparts. This Agreement may be executed in one or more counterparts, each of which when so executed shall be deemed an original, and all of which when taken together shall constitute one and the same instrument.
6.14 Resolution of Disputes. Any dispute or controversy arising under this Agreement, its application or interpretation ("Dispute") shall be settled definitively .and exclusively in accordance with the following procedure.
6.14.1 The Dispute ·will first be reviewed by one member of management designated for the purpose of each of Party. It is the intention of the Parties that the designated managers shall, within thirty (30) days of designation, devise a mutually agreeable solution for acceptance by both Parties.
6.14.2 If the designated managers are unable to devise an acceptable solution within thirty (30) days, or if the Parties both do not accept the solution proposed, the Dispute shall be submitted to the Chief Executive
Officer ("CEO") of NextEra Energy Resources, LLC for resolution. The CEO may resolve the dispute personally or appoint an individual or a committee to resolve the Dispute. In delegating his authority, the CEO may impose any deadlines or direct the utilization of such procedures, if any, as he deems appropriate. The decision of the CEO or his designee shall be final and binding on both parties.
[SIGNATURE PAGE FOLLOWS]
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, the Parties have caused this Shared Facilities Agreement to be executed as of the date first written above.

EXHIBIT A TO SHARED FACILITIES AGREEMENT
The “Shared Facilities” shall consist of the interconnection facilities and related facilities and equipment identified in Appendices A (Interconnection Facilities, Network Upgrades and Distribution Upgrades and C (Interconnection Details of the GIA, excluding metering equipment.
